`fetch_forge_refs` uses the refspec `+refs/forge/*:refs/forge/*`. The leading `+` forces the fetch, unconditionally overwriting all local forge refs with the remote state. Any issues or comments created with `--no-push` are silently destroyed the next time a command runs without `--no-push`.

The refspec should not use `+` (or should be replaced with a merge/fast-forward-only strategy) so that local-only refs are not clobbered by a fetch.

